# Leave everything below unset to run locally with zero setup: NuxtHub gives
# you a real local Postgres database for free (PGlite, stored in `.data/`),
# and the dashboard serves generated sample data until it sees its first real
# event (no login screen either, without ANALYTICS_PASSWORD). Fill these in
# to connect a production store and lock the dashboard down before deploying.

# Connection string for the production Postgres store (auto-injected when you
# add a Marketplace Postgres integration through the "Deploy with Vercel"
# button — copy the exact variable name it creates if it differs, e.g.
# POSTGRES_URL / POSTGRESQL_URL, both are also recognised). Unset locally —
# NuxtHub falls back to a local PGlite database automatically.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/db

# Shared password for the dashboard login. Unset = no login required.
# Pick something long and random once you deploy this for real.
# ANALYTICS_PASSWORD=change-me

# Session signing secret required by nuxt-auth-utils. Must be 32+ random
# characters — NOT the same value as ANALYTICS_PASSWORD, and never typed into
# the login form. Only needed once ANALYTICS_PASSWORD is set — auto-generated
# in dev otherwise. A value shorter than 32 chars breaks login with a generic
# "Invalid password" error even when ANALYTICS_PASSWORD is correct.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
# NUXT_SESSION_PASSWORD=

# Optional: comma-separated tool names accepted by /api/telemetry/ingest.
# Defaults to "evlog-cli" when unset.
# ANALYTICS_ALLOWED_TOOLS=evlog-cli,my-other-tool

# Optional: JSON map of extra allowlisted custom field keys per tool,
# merged on top of the built-in defaults (see server/utils/allowed-tools.ts).
# ANALYTICS_ALLOWED_CUSTOM_KEYS={"my-other-tool":["itemsSynced"]}

# Optional: force mock/sample data on ("1") even once the `runs` table has
# real rows, or force it off ("0") — e.g. to see the real "no data" empty
# states instead of the sample dataset. Auto-detected (empty table → mock)
# otherwise.
# ANALYTICS_MOCK_DATA=
